'''Juan Agustín Musso''' (born 6 May 1994) is an Argentine professional [[footballer]] who plays as a [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for {{Spanish football updater|Atlético Madrid}} club [[Atlético Madrid]] and the [[Argentina national football team|Argentina national team]].

==Club career==
Musso trained at the academy of Club de Regatas San Nicolas, before going on loan to [[Defensores de Belgrano de Villa Ramallo]], with which he won the local championship at the age of 16. In the final, he saved three out of five penalties in the [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|shoot-out]].{{Citation needed|date=July 2021}}

===Racing Club===
Musso was the third-choice goalkeeper during [[Racing Club de Avellaneda|Racing Club]]'s [[2014 Argentine Primera División]] championship, the team's first title in 13 years. He made his professional debut [[2016–17 Argentine Primera División|three years later]], on 28 May 2017, in a 2–1 home win against [[San Lorenzo de Almagro|San Lorenzo]]. Musso became the team's first-choice goalkeeper during the [[2017–18 Argentine Primera División]], in which Racing finished in 7th place and qualified for the [[2019 Copa Sudamericana]].{{Citation needed|date=July 2021}}

===Udinese===
In the summer of 2018, Musso was signed by [[Serie A]] side [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]]. Throughout the season, he established himself as the undisputed starter and became one of the team's key players. In three seasons, Musso accumulated a total of 102 appearances in the league.<ref name=stats/>

===Atalanta===
On 2 July 2021, Musso was signed by [[Atalanta BC|Atalanta]].<ref name=atalanta-benvenuto>{{Cite web|title=Benvenuto Musso!|trans-title=Welcome, Musso!|url=https://www.atalanta.it/news/benvenuto-musso/ |publisher=Atalanta BC|date=2 July 2021|language=it}}</ref> On 22 May 2024, he clinched his first trophy with the club as Atalanta defeated [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]] to win the [[2023–24 UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League]].

===Atlético Madrid===
On 27 August 2024, Musso joined [[La Liga]] club [[Atlético Madrid]] on a season-long loan for the 2024–25 season.<ref>{{cite web |title=Welcome, Juan Musso! |url=https://en.atleticodemadrid.com/noticias/welcome-juan-musso |publisher=Atlético Madrid |access-date=27 August 2024 |date=27 August 2024 }}</ref>

On 10 June 2025, Atlético Madrid made the transfer permanent and signed a three-season contract with Musso.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Atlético Madrid|url=https://en.atleticodemadrid.com/noticias/agreement-with-atalanta-for-the-transfer-of-juan-musso|title=Agreement with Atalanta for the transfer of Juan Musso|date=10 June 2025|access-date=6 July 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Musso was born in Argentina and is of Italian descent, holding both passports.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Chi è Juan Musso|url=https://www.gazzettadelfantacalcio.it/2018/07/17/chi-e-juan-musso/|website=Gazzetta del Fanta Calcio|date=17 July 2018|language=it|access-date=4 April 2019|archive-date=4 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190404045314/https://www.gazzettadelfantacalcio.it/2018/07/17/chi-e-juan-musso/|url-status=dead}}</ref> He was part of the [[Argentina national under-20 football team|Argentina U20 national team]]'s squad for the [[2013 South American Youth Football Championship]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/team/squad/_/id/2840/league/CONMEBOL.SUDAMERICANO_SUB20/season/2013 |title=Argentina U20 2013 CONMEBOL Sudamericano Sub-20 Squad |publisher=ESPN |access-date=June 10, 2024}}</ref>

On 26 March 2019, Musso debuted for the [[Argentina national football team|Argentine senior squad]] in a [[Exhibition match#Association football|friendly match]] against [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]], coming as a 67th-minute [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Esteban Andrada]].<ref>{{Cite news|first=Marcos|last=Durán|title=Correa fue Messi en Marruecos|url=https://argentina.as.com/argentina/2019/03/26/futbol/1553634800_797227.html|website=[[Diario AS]]|date=26 March 2019|language=es|quote=También hizo su debut en la selección Juan Musso. El del Udinese entró a los 67 minutos por Andrada. Debut plácido del de Boca, que a pesar del clima no tuvo muchos inconvenientes en mostrarse seguro.|trans-quote=Juan Musso also debuted for the national team. The Udinese player came on in the 67th minute for Andrada. A placid debut, he did not have many problems in being confident despite the weather.}}</ref> The same year on 14 June, Musso received a late call-up for the [[2019 Copa América]] to replace the injured Andrada.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Argentine Football Association|AFA]]|url=https://www.afa.com.ar/es/posts/parte-medico-de-esteban-andrada|title=Parte médico de Esteban Andrada|date=14 June 2019}}</ref>

